article.headline: Morehead State 80, Asbury 57
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Shaun Williams scored 18 points to lead Morehead State to an 80-57 win Monday over Asbury College. Brandon Callahan scored 14 for Morehead (1-1), Quentin Pryor added 13 and Cordaryl Ballard 11. Michael Spann led Asbury (2-3) with 15 points on 5-of-6 shooting from 3-point range. Derek Bland added 12 points. Spann hit a 3-pointer with 8:35 left in the first half to draw Asbury within three points at 23-20, but Morehead State pulled out to a 47-37 lead at halftime. The Eagles went on an 11-4 run to start the second half and held Asbury scoreless for 7:22 in the final stretch for the win. Morehead forced Asbury into 26 turnovers, which the Eagles turned into 29 points, and outscored Asbury 42-16 in the paint.
